Sentencas: A cermet-supported tubular SOFC was fabricated using thermal spray.
Titulo: Effect of Gas Pressure on Polarization of SOFC Cathode Prepared by Plasma Spray

Sentencas: The cell performance was investigated at temperatures from 750 to 900 degrees C and pressures from 0.1 to 0.5 MPa to examine the effect of operating gas pressure on the cell performance.
Titulo: Effect of Gas Pressure on Polarization of SOFC Cathode Prepared by Plasma Spray

Sentencas: The influence of gas pressure on the cathodic polarization was studied through the electrochemical impedance approach to examine the controlling electrochemical processes during cell operation.
Titulo: Effect of Gas Pressure on Polarization of SOFC Cathode Prepared by Plasma Spray

Sentencas: Results show that increasing the operating gas pressure improves the power output performance significantly.
Titulo: Effect of Gas Pressure on Polarization of SOFC Cathode Prepared by Plasma Spray

Sentencas: When the gas pressure is increased from 0.1 to 0.3 MPa, the maximum power density is increased by a factor of 32% at a temperature of 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Effect of Gas Pressure on Polarization of SOFC Cathode Prepared by Plasma Spray

Sentencas: The cathode polarization decreases significantly with the increase of the gas pressure.
Titulo: Effect of Gas Pressure on Polarization of SOFC Cathode Prepared by Plasma Spray

Sentencas: The electrochemical analysis shows that the main control processes of the cathode reaction are the oxygen species transfer at the three-phase boundary and oxygen diffusion on the surface or in the bulk of the cathode, which are enhanced with increasing gas pressure.
Titulo: Effect of Gas Pressure on Polarization of SOFC Cathode Prepared by Plasma Spray
